Execution

Usage:
eventHunter -i input_event_interface [-x]
-i set the input event interface for your specified device.
-x output information for all the events.
-w the gesture generating eg. SWIPING/ZOOMING/SWIPE
-o the orientation of the flip eg. L means vertical
Example: 
./eventHunter -i /dev/input/event3 -x (means starting eventHunter by hooking to /dev/input/event3)
___________________________________________________________________________________
eventHunter is a tool used to hook to one input device for event listening/sending.
